#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.49:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.49:0.2"
msgid "5. Attadīpavagga"
msgstr "5. Be Your Own Island"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.49:0.3"
msgid "49. Soṇasutta"
msgstr "49. With Soṇa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn22.49:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn22.49:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho soṇo gahapatiputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe …"
msgstr "Then the householder Soṇa went up to the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:1.4"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho soṇaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi keci, soṇa, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aniccena rūpena dukkhena "
"vipariṇāmadhammena ‘seyyohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""
"“Soṇa, there are ascetics and brahmins who—based on form, which is "
"impermanent, suffering, and perishable—regard themselves thus: ‘I’m better’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.2"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m equal’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.3"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m worse’."

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.4"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa adassanā?"
msgstr "What is that but a failure to see truly?"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.5"
msgid ""
"Aniccāya vedanāya dukkhāya vipariṇāmadhammāya ‘seyyohamasmī’ti vā "
"samanupassanti;"
msgstr "Based on feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.6"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.7"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.8"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa adassanā?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.9"
msgid "Aniccāya saññāya …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.10"
msgid ""
"aniccehi saṅkhārehi dukkhehi vipariṇāmadhammehi ‘seyyohamasmī’ti vā "
"samanupassanti;"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.11"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.12"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.13"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa adassanā?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.14"
msgid ""
"Aniccena viññāṇena dukkhena vipariṇāmadhammena ‘seyyohamasmī’ti vā "
"samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""
"consciousness, which is impermanent, suffering, and perishable, they regard "
"themselves thus: ‘I’m better’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.15"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m equal’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.16"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’ti vā samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m worse’."

msgctxt "sn22.49:2.17"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa adassanā?"
msgstr "What is that but a failure to see truly?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.49"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:3.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, soṇa, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aniccena rūpena dukkhena "
"vipariṇāmadhammena ‘seyyohamasmī’tipi na samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who—based on form, which is impermanent, "
"suffering, and perishable—don’t regard themselves thus: ‘I’m better’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.2"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’tipi na samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m equal’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.3"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’tipi na samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m worse’."

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.4"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa dassanā?"
msgstr "What is that but seeing truly?"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.5"
msgid "Aniccāya vedanāya …"
msgstr "Based on feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.6"
msgid "aniccāya saññāya …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.7"
msgid "aniccehi saṅkhārehi …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.8"
msgid ""
"aniccena viññāṇena dukkhena vipariṇāmadhammena ‘seyyohamasmī’tipi na "
"samanupassanti;"
msgstr ""
"consciousness, which is impermanent, suffering, and perishable, they don’t "
"regard themselves thus: ‘I’m better’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.9"
msgid "‘sadisohamasmī’tipi na samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m equal’,"

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.10"
msgid "‘hīnohamasmī’tipi na samanupassanti;"
msgstr "or ‘I’m worse’."

msgctxt "sn22.49:3.11"
msgid "kimaññatra yathābhūtassa dassanā?"
msgstr "What is that but seeing truly?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, soṇa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Soṇa? "

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.9"
msgid "“Vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.10"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.11"
msgid "“saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.12"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.13"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.14"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.15"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.16"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.17"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.18"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.49:4.19"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, soṇa, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So, Soṇa, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am "
"not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.50"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:6.1"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā …"
msgstr "You should truly see any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:6.2"
msgid "yā kāci saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:6.3"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.49:6.4"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘"
"netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.49:7.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, soṇa, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.49:7.2"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn22.49:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.49:7.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
